 my tests and ensure the method filtering won’t miss important overrides. Resetting streams before stopping the appender could be a concern too.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering placeholder tests**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m evaluating the appender tests and whether to keep or remove placeholder tests that only serve as scaffolding. If the assertion fails, it looks like the appender resets, which complicates things. The placeholder test might not be necessary anymore since it doesn’t add real value. I could simply delete it to avoid clutter. However, I wonder if removing too many placeholder tests could lead to a lack of generic classes. Since we need to improve coverage, removing it seems like the best move.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Deciding on placeholder removal**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI need to ensure that there are no issues with having \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"all top-level test classes public,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" so I don't want to make unnecessary edits. Since we’ve already modified some parts, I'm leaning towards deleting the placeholder test since it's tracked. It seems like removing it to tidy things up is a good plan. The ConsoleAppenderTest is in place, so I think it’s safe to proceed with the removal using bash. It’ll help avoid scaffold-only tests.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_JBfBUpu4NvrLIS12MeQjJHJQ|fc_0a05747ff7814e5b0169f717a053ec81968a024444c93cca45\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"bash\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"command\\\": \\\"rm tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26/src/test/java/ch_qos_logback/logback_core/Logback_coreTest.java\\\"}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 1574, \\\"output\\\": 549, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 29184, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 31307, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"inpu